The circumference `c` of the earth at the equator in meters, divided by two, twenty five times is roughly one point two meters `s`.

```js
const c = 40075017
const s = 1.1943285763263702
const n = c / s
const dlon = 360 / n
return `${n} segments of ${dlon} degrees longitude`
